{{Infobox recurring event |name = Greater Gulf State Fair |logo = |image = |caption = |location = [[Mobile, Alabama]] |years_active = {{Age in years|1955}} |dates = late October |genre = [[Agricultural Show|Agricultural]] |website = http://thegroundsmobile.com/ }}
The '''Greater Gulf State Fair''' is an annual [[fair]] and [[agricultural show]] that is held at the Greater Gulf State Fairgrounds in [[Mobile, Alabama|Mobile]], [[Alabama]]. It features [[livestock]] competitions, [[roller coasters|rides]], concessions, motor contests, and concerts. It has been held every year since 1955, and moved to its current location in 1974. The event's name stems from its serving of people from [[Lower Alabama]], [[Lower Mississippi]], and the [[Panhandle of Florida]]. It is the largest fair in the state of Alabama.
==Background== The Greater Gulf State Fair began as a fund-raising initiative for the Mobile Jaycees, a group of members of the Mobile Junior Chamber of Commerce.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://thegroundsmobile.com/content/ggsf-1.html|title=The Greater Gulf State Fair|publisher=TheGroundsMobile.com|accessdate=July 14, 2017}}</ref> It was first held at [[Blakeley Island (Alabama)|Blakeley Island]] in 1955,<ref name="al"/> and drew 60,000 people in its inaugural year.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=yCEEAAAAMBAJ|title=Mobile, Ala. Pulls 60,000 To Maiden Run|date=November 12, 1955|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|The Billboard]]|issn=0006-2510|pages=136|volume=67|issue=46|accessdate=July 14, 2017}}</ref> [[Elvis Presley]] was the first concert performer, and offered them a four-year contract to return, but the Fair declined. With the event gaining success, the Jaycees hired a president to oversee planning in 1958.<ref name="al"/> During these years, the event took place at [[Ladd Stadium]], and later at Hartwell Field in Mobile.<ref name="bb">{{cite news|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=FCAEAAAAMBAJ|title=Free Name Act Show Boosts Mobile Fair|date=October 24, 1960|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|The Billboard]]|issn=0006-2510|pages=56–58|volume=72|issue=4|accessdate=July 14, 2017}}</ref> In 1974, the Fair moved to its permanent residence at the Greater Gulf State Fairgrounds in west Mobile. It was renamed "the Grounds" in 2014.
The rides present at each Fair are a combination of the Fair that begins in [[Canada]], travels down opposite seaboards, and regroups in Mobile.<ref name="al">{{cite news|url=http://www.al.com/entertainment/index.ssf/2014/10/60th_greater_gulf_state_fair_i.html|title=60th Greater Gulf State Fair in Mobile focuses on the family|date=October 29, 2014|work=[[Press-Register]]|publisher=AL.com|author=Angela Lewis|accessdate=July 14, 2017}}</ref>
